benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/invoiceItems/{invoiceItemId}/auditLogsWithHistory - Retrieve invoice item audit logs with history by id

covered: GET Valid Request: 200 with JSON array of AuditLog objects and required fields (TC01).
Empty Response: 200 with empty array when no logs exist (TC02).
Path parameter validation: malformed/partial UUID returns 400 (TC04, TC17).
Resource not found: 404 for non-existent item and empty DB (TC03, TC18).
Authorization: 401 for missing and invalid/expired tokens (TC05, TC06).
Query Parameters: Unsupported extras are ignored with 200 (TC07).
Performance/Scalability: large history and load response times checked (TC09, TC15).
Concurrency: concurrent reads return consistent 200 and bodies (TC14).
Security hardening: SQL injection and XSS attempts safely handled (TC10, TC11).
Regression and backward compatibility covered (TC12, TC13).
gaps: Pagination: No validation of pagination or limits for large result sets (if supported).
Rate Limiting: No tests for burst traffic/429 or rate-limit headers.
Caching Behavior: No checks for ETag/Last-Modified, Cache-Control, or conditional GET (If-None-Match/If-Modified-Since).
Authorization granularity: No 403/role- or tenant-based access coverage (if applicable).
Query Parameters breadth: No scenarios for documented valid params, sorting, or ordering (if any).
Error response schema: Negative cases do not validate standard error structure/fields.
Data correctness details: No explicit checks for chronological order, item ID association on each AuditLog, or timestamp format.
Observability/headers: No verification of Date, request-id/correlation-id headers.
Server error path: No explicit 500 Internal Server Error coverage.
recommendations: Add pagination scenarios for large histories: limit/offset defaults, boundaries, last-page and invalid values.
Introduce rate limiting tests: sustained bursts leading to 429 with verification of rate-limit and retry-after headers.
Validate caching: assert ETag/Cache-Control presence and perform conditional GETs expecting 304 Not Modified.
Expand authorization tests to include 403 for insufficient permissions or wrong tenant (if applicable).
Cover any supported query params (filters/order); if none, assert consistent rejection/ignoring of unknowns.
Assert standard error schema for 400/401/404/503: error code, message, and correlation ID.
Strengthen data assertions: each entry ties to the invoiceItemId, correct chronological order, complete fields per #/definitions/AuditLog, ISO-8601 timestamps/timezones.
Add header/perf checks: Date header present, gzip/br compression supported, and objective SLA thresholds.
Include a 500 error simulation to verify generic server error handling.
